Rescue workers searching the rubble of buildings destroyed by the explosion that rocked Abule-Ado in the Amuwo-Odofin Local Government Area of Lagos State, on Monday, recovered the bodies of three more victims of the incident. The corpses were recovered from the rubble of some of the collapsed buildings at the Bethlehem Girls College in Abule-Ado. Officials of the school confirmed the identity of the corpses to be workers of Bethlehem Girls College. The corpses consist of two females and one male. Hundreds of residents in the area had on Sunday been rendered homeless following the explosion which destroyed so many homes and claimed several lives. Some residents of the area were seen parking rummaging through the rubble to salvage some of their belongings. Operatives of the FRSC, LASEMA, the Nigerian Red Cross, police, Federal and State Fire Service as well as Lagos State Neigbourhood Safety Corps were still at the scene of the incident to carry out rescue operations. The state Chairman, Nigerian Red Cross, Adebola Kolawole, confirmed the recovery of the three corpses. 